           <div type="translation">
                <p>                    To the Manes Gods! Iulius Ponticus, who lived 32 years and served in the Fifth Macedonian legion 14 years, was born in Amastris (Pontus et Bithynia province, Paphlagonia region). His "brothers" and heirs raised the monument to the well-deserving on their own expenses: Iulius Ponticus, brother; Sentius Ponticus, veteran; Sentius Ponticus soldier of the Fifth Macedonian legion.</p>
